               <p>JOSEPH BAILEY. I am a <rs id="t18280911-263-viclabel1351" type="occupation">warehouseman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-263-victim1465 t18280911-263-viclabel1351"></join>, and live in Lad-lane. On the 30th of July, about four o'clock, I was in <placeName id="t18280911-263-crimeloc1352">Goswell-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-263-crimeloc1352" type="placeName" value="Goswell-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-263-crimeloc1352" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-263-off1349 t18280911-263-crimeloc1352"></join>; I felt a pull at my pocket - turned round, and saw the prisoner with my handkerchief in his coat - I had used it about two minutes before; I took hold of him, and he dropped it down; I took it up - I know it to be mine - it has my mark on it - I have made enquiry respecting his friends, and find they are very respectable.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-263-person1466">
                  JAMES 
                  CLIFFORD
               <interp inst="t18280911-263-person1466" type="surname" value="CLIFFORD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-263-person1466" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-263-person1466" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I was sent for and took the prisoner.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. There was a caravan at the corner of Sutton-street; the horse would not go on - there was a mob; I stopped where this gentleman turned round and accused me of taking his handkerchief, which I never had.</p>
               <p>One witness gave the prisoner a good character.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 14.</p>
               <p>Recommended to Mercy by the Jury - <rs id="t18280911-263-verdict1353" type="verdictDescription">
